Live 2021 Election Turnout Tracker

Welcome to the Sixty-Six Wards Turnout Tracker! Voters across Philadelphia are sharing their turnout to support citizen science.

First, vote! Then, share your division and Voter Number at bit.ly/sixtysixturnout .

Live Results

As of 2:48 PM, 319 voters in 57 wards have shared their voter number. I estimate that 228,322 people have voted in person across the city (95% Confidence Interval: 202,015 - 252,769). In addition, more than 351,000 mail-in ballots have already been returned*, and -351,000 are still outstanding.

NOTE: The above mail counts are received from the Commissioners’ Office. Some mail-ins that have already arrived are probably not included in this projection. In addition, ballots postmarked today that haven’t arrived yet are not included.

Maps

I use historic correlations among divisions’ turnout to estimate turnout in the divisions with no data yet. I simultaneously estimate (1) the overall city-wide turnout, (2) divisions’ over-/under-performance, and (3) the city-wide time pattern of voting. See the Methodology.
